Text processing
\layout Standard

Basic Uplug operations are done by calling the 
\family typewriter 
uplug
\family default 
 script, using various configuration files (located in $UPLUG_HOME/systems).
\layout Subsection

Tokenization
\layout Standard

To use the tagging and alignment functions, the corpus has to be tokenized,
 and converted to XML:
\layout LyX-Code

$ uplug $UPLUGHOME/systems/pre/basic -in 1988sv.txt > 1988sv.xml
\layout Standard

Unless you want to use the default utf8 charset, you can specify charsets
 with the 
\family typewriter 
-ci
\family default 
 (input charset) and 
\family typewriter 
-co
\family default 
 (output charset) options:
\layout LyX-Code

$ uplug $UPLUGHOME/systems/pre/basic -co 'iso-8859-1' -ci 'iso-8859-1' -in
 1988sv.txt > 1988sv.xml
